The paper deals with mechanism design and matching problems, which are typically studied in the game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of online bipartite matching suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), while the analysis of social welfare and efficiency is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
